The Declamator however does not say that all Italia brought him back on her shoulders: it brought him back ‘paene suis humeris! So Marius did not destroy all the Senate, but ‘cunctum senatum paene delevit ;' and the men were not called up from Acheron (c. 10), but ‘ paene ex Ache- ronte excitatos? and he goes on in the same way all through these speeches (De Domo, c. 51).
